  The files created with M&M are freely distributable.

  The programs "MMPlayer", "MMReq" and "MMAnalyse" are public domain
  and freely distributable.


@{u}@{fg fill}This program is SHAREWARE!@{uu}@{fg text}

  The menu-projects created by this unregistered version of "MMEditor"
  are showing a requester at every start and will produce slightly
  crippled menus.

  If you like M&M and plan to use the menus created with it,
  you have to register.

  After registration, you will get a @{b}keyfile@{ub} which will prevent
  the requesters from appearing.


@{u}@{fg fill}How can I install M&M?@{uu}@{fg text}

  For installation purpose start the menu-project "@{b}Install.M&M@{ub}"
  by double-clicking.

  ATTENTION: To run the installation routine, the ARexx system
             should be started before!

  More hints concerning the installation can be found
  in the M&M.guide.


@{u}@{fg fill}How can I get more information about M&M?@{uu}@{fg text}

  You can access more information by starting "MMEditor" and
  pressing the HELP key. The M&M documentation guide will appear.

  If you have questions, please write to me - but include a SAE!
  You can also send me an eMail (address below)


@{u}@{fg fill}How can I get the full version of M&M?@{uu}@{fg text}

  You can access a registered full version of M&M from:

    Axel Sodtalbers
    Philipp-Reis-Strasse 2-49
    37075 Goettingen
    Germany

    Internet eMail: asodtal@gwdg.de


  The fee: Ł15 (GB) or US$30 (other)

  Please @{fg shine}pay cash@{fg text} - no more euro-cheques accepted!

  Bank: Sparkasse Aurich, BLZ 28451050, Konto Nr. 111008462


@{u}@{fg fill}The Versions:@{uu}@{fg text}

  Version 3.13:   * more than 25 new ARexx Commands
                  * Automatic project installation within MMEditor
                  * complete new project examples
                  * Individual setting of the bit-planes used by
                    MMEditor
                  * New Dos Command-Option: Set WaitPointer
                  * || as linefeed in requester texts
                  * improved error messages
                  * request before MMEditor executes a startup-command

  Version 3.14    * no more problems with asyncron running dos commands
                  * error in installation.rexx fixed

  Version 3.20    * New command: Show Brush (also via ARexx commands)
                  * Much improved IFF ILBM reading routine
                    with correct 32 bit (AGA) colortable reading
                  * New options when running dos commands:
                    Priority and Current directory
                  * Possibilty to clear all environment variables used by
                    MMPlayer when quitting the menu
                  * Testrun gadget in the Screens-Window
                  * better requester positioning

  @{"Version 3.21 - the current one" link "TheNews" 0}
@endnode

@node "TheNews" "The News..."

   @{u}@{fg fill}New in Version 3.21:@{uu}@{fg text}

   · Iconify (with or without AppIcon, via ARexx)

   · Small editor for requester texts

   · now | (instead of ||) as linefeeder in requester texts

   · after screen loading error, possibilty to select
     an alternative menu screen

   · pulldown menus: real intuition barlabels supported

   · new Arexx commands for an easy way of launching
     a shell or an editor

   · MMEditor can be started with system font or topaz.8
     (ToolType TOPAZEIGHT)

   · completely new designed examples

   · MagicWB Icons

   · bug fix
@endnode

